"```sql\nSELECT \n    Segment, \n    (SUM(CASE WHEN Date = '201301' THEN Consumption ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN Date = '201205' THEN Consumption ELSE 0 END)) AS Consumption_Increase,\n    (SUM(CASE WHEN Date = '201301' THEN Consumption ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN Date = '201205' THEN Consumption ELSE 0 END)) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN Date = '201301' THEN Consumption ELSE 0 END), 0) * 100 AS Percentage_Increase\nFROM \n    yearmonth \nJOIN \n    customers ON yearmonth.CustomerID = customers.CustomerID\nWHERE \n    Date IN ('201205', '201301') \nGROUP BY \n    Segment\nORDER BY \n    Percentage_Increase DESC\nLIMIT 1;\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the percentage increase in consumption for each segment (SME, LAM, KAM) between May 2012 and January 2013, and orders the results to find the segment with the highest percentage increase. To find the segment with the lowest percentage increase, you can modify the `ORDER BY` clause to `ORDER BY Percentage_Increase ASC LIMIT 1;`."